recapArticle.title: New England Revolution 2, Columbus Crew 1 | MLS Match Recap

timelineItems.desc: A huge encounter in the Eastern Conference is ahead on Saturday evening as the New England Revolution return home to take on the Columbus Crew at Gillette Stadium.
timelineItems.title: KICKOFF: New England Revolution vs Columbus Crew | October 4, 2014

timelineItems.comment: First Half begins.

timelineItems.name: Paula Ramsay
timelineItems.text: @ColumbusCrew Is it as cold there tonite as it is here in Ohio??? #Crew96

timelineItems.comment: Attempt missed. Ethan Finlay (Columbus Crew) right footed shot from the left side of the box is close, but misses to the right. Assisted by Tony Tchani with a through ball.

timelineItems.name: Jim Caulfield
timelineItems.text: Guess the guy that waters the turf is off tonight. #nerevs

timelineItems.comment: Delay in match Kelyn Rowe (New England Revolution) because of an injury.
Delay in match Federico Higuaín (Columbus Crew) because of an injury.
Lineups are announced and players are warming up.

timelineItems.name: Matt LaPan
timelineItems.text: Farrell has been all over the field early #RandomThought #NERevs

timelineItems.name: Taylor Twellman
timelineItems.text: Hey @AlexiLalas do the @Patriots play tomorrow?! #NEvCLB

timelineItems.name: Bill Doyle
timelineItems.text: Absolutely painful to watch @NERevolution play with all that NFL crap all over the pitch. Jermaine Jones must be horrified. #NERevs

timelineItems.comment: Delay over. They are ready to continue.
Corner,  New England Revolution. Conceded by Waylon Francis.

timelineItems.name: Daniel Karell
timelineItems.text: Very dangerous challenge from Higuain, who stepped on the shins of Rowe. Could have been a card easily. #Crew96

timelineItems.comment: Delay in match Justin Meram (Columbus Crew) because of an injury.
Delay over. They are ready to continue.

José Gonçalves (New England Revolution) wins a free kick in the defensive half.
Foul by Ethan Finlay (Columbus Crew).

timelineItems.name: Craig Forde
timelineItems.text: The #NERevs did train in dismal conditions much of the week, but nothing like tonight. Fans gutting this one out deserve praise

timelineItems.comment: Foul by Wil Trapp (Columbus Crew).
Jermaine Jones (New England Revolution) wins a free kick on the left wing.

timelineItems.name: Cathal Conlon
timelineItems.text: It takes more than a little bit of rain to dampen the enthusiasm of #NERevs fans. Great buzz in the building tonight. Well played!

timelineItems.name: Margaret Rose
timelineItems.text: #NERevs

timelineItems.comment: Attempt missed. Teal Bunbury (New England Revolution) right footed shot from the right side of the box is just a bit too high. Assisted by Charlie Davies.

timelineItems.desc: Attempt saved. Aaron Schoenfeld (Columbus Crew) right footed shot from the center of the box is saved in the bottom right corner.
timelineItems.title: SAVE: Bobby Shuttleworth gets down quick to stop Aaron Schoenfeld

timelineItems.name: Carl Setterlund
timelineItems.text: That run by Davies tho #NERevs #NEvCLB

timelineItems.comment: Attempt saved. Aaron Schoenfeld (Columbus Crew) right footed shot from the centre of the box is saved in the bottom right corner. Assisted by Ethan Finlay.

timelineItems.name: Seth
timelineItems.text: Weird to see Jones openly standing offside on the free kick. Did it last week too #NERevs

timelineItems.name: Matt Bernhardt
timelineItems.text: If you hear random crowd noise on the broadcast, Horse Guy was just on the jumbotron #crew96

timelineItems.name: Ryan Schwepfinger
timelineItems.text: Unreal save by Shuttleworth. #Crew96 buildup was tremendous. Just keep plugging away and it'll come.

timelineItems.name: Jimmy Nelson
timelineItems.text: WHAT A SAVE!! Shuttleworth had some nasty words for his defenders. #NERevs

timelineItems.name: Fierce Kierce
timelineItems.text: Um excuse me, where is the defense? Thank god Bobby is paying attention. #nerevs

timelineItems.desc: Goal!  New England Revolution 1, Columbus Crew 0. Lee Nguyen (New England Revolution) right footed shot from the center of the box to the bottom right.
timelineItems.title: GOAL: Lee Nguyen finds space and gives the Revs the lead

timelineItems.comment: Attempt missed. Federico Higuaín (Columbus Crew) right footed shot from more than 35 yards is just a bit too high. Assisted by Justin Meram.

timelineItems.name: WrongSideOfThePond
timelineItems.text: Ugh... THOSE football lines. #NERevs

timelineItems.name: Dave Edinger
timelineItems.text: #Crew96 really struggling in the red zone. 0 for 3. #gridironlines

timelineItems.comment: Match ends, New England Revolution 2, Columbus Crew 1.

timelineItems.name: Matt LaPan
timelineItems.text: That does it! Revs win 2-1 behind Jermaine Jones' game-winner for the 2nd straight match #NERevs

timelineItems.name: Scott Wesseler
timelineItems.text: Whelp, let's just attribute this #Crew96 loss to turf? Cool? Cool.

timelineItems.name: Murph
timelineItems.text: @LeeNguyen24 @Jermainejunior and @b_shuttle Made this game! Good job #NERevs

timelineItems.name: Matt Bernhardt
timelineItems.text: #crew96 struggled for much of the game, and can't complain about this result - lack of discipline and control, IMO

timelineItems.name: Ryan Schwepfinger

timelineItems.name: Bob Zeserson
timelineItems.text: What a clutch win #NERevs tonight, back in 2nd place, 3 games until the playoffs and the march to #mlscup2014

timelineItems.desc: A huge encounter in the Eastern Conference is ahead on Saturday evening as the New England Revolution return home to take on the Columbus Crew at Gillette Stadium.
timelineItems.title: HIGHLIGHTS: New England Revolution vs Columbus Crew | October 4, 2013

timelineItems.name: Tim Fontenault
timelineItems.text: Lee Nguyen scores. No one is surprised. #LeeNguyenForUSMNT #LeeNguyenForMLSMVP #NERevs

timelineItems.text: #nerevs
